@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy & Security";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
}
  <main id="privacy-main">
    <header>
        <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>
        <p>Last updated: 15 November 2025</p>
    </header>

    <section id="introduction">
      <h2>Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        We value your trust. Protecting your personal information and ensuring secure access to our services is a priority.
        This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you interact with our website, catalog, and reservation system.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="data-controller">
      <h2>Data controller</h2>
      <p>
        The Board Game Library (the “Library”) is the data controller responsible for processing your personal data on this website.
        If the Library operates within an institution, the institution may also act as a joint controller for certain processes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="information-we-collect">
      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Account details:</strong>
          Name, email address, and password (stored as a secure hash).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reservation data:</strong>
          Titles you borrow, reservation dates, pickup/return status, and overdue flags.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Communication records:</strong>
          Messages, feedback, and support requests sent via forms or email.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Technical data:</strong>
          IP address, browser type, device information, and anonymized usage statistics (e.g., pages visited, session duration).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies and similar technologies:</strong>
          Essential cookies for authentication and session management; optional analytics cookies if you consent.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="legal-bases">
      <h2>Legal bases for processing (GDPR)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Contract:</strong>
          To provide account functionality and manage reservations you request.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Consent:</strong>
          For optional communications (e.g., newsletters) and non-essential cookies/analytics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legitimate interests:</strong>
          To improve the website, ensure service integrity, and prevent misuse.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal obligation:</strong>
          To comply with applicable laws and institutional policies.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="how-we-use">
      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account management:</strong> Create and maintain your user account and authentication.</li>
        <li><strong>Reservations and notifications:</strong> Process reservations, manage pickups/returns, and send status updates.</li>
        <li><strong>Service improvements:</strong> Analyze anonymized usage to enhance catalog, search, and site performance.</li>
        <li><strong>Security and integrity:</strong> Monitor for fraud or abuse and protect our systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Enforce library rules and meet legal requirements.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal data to third parties and do not share it for marketing purposes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="data-sharing">
      <h2>Data sharing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Service providers:</strong>
          Trusted vendors (e.g., hosting, email delivery) may process data on our behalf under data processing agreements.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Institutional partners:</strong>
          Where applicable, limited sharing with institutional IT or administration to support operations and compliance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Legal requirements:</strong>
          Disclosure if required by law, regulation, or a valid legal process.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="security-measures">
      <h2>Security measures</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Encryption in transit:</strong> HTTPS/TLS for all website communications.</li>
        <li><strong>Secure password storage:</strong> Industry-standard hashing and salting; never store plain-text passwords.</li>
        <li><strong>Access controls:</strong> Role-based access; only authorized staff can view reservation records.</li>
        <li><strong>System hardening:</strong> Regular updates, patching, and monitoring to prevent unauthorized access.</li>
        <li><strong>Backups and continuity:</strong> Periodic backups and recovery procedures to protect against data loss.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="retention">
      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account data:</strong> Kept while your account is active; removed or anonymized upon request or inactivity after a defined period.</li>
        <li><strong>Reservation records:</strong> Retained for operational and audit purposes for a limited time, then anonymized.</li>
        <li><strong>Communications:</strong> Retained as long as necessary to address your request and for compliance.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> Stored in aggregate or anonymized form when feasible.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="your-rights">
      <h2>Your rights (EU/EEA)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of your personal data we hold.</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Ask us to correct inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your data, subject to legal obligations.</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Ask us to limit processing under certain conditions.</li>
        <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Receive your data in a structured, commonly used format.</li>
        <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing based on legitimate interests or direct marketing.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdraw consent:</strong> Withdraw consent for optional processing at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Complaint:</strong> Lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="cookies">
      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Required for login, session state, and security.</li>
        <li><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> Optional settings (e.g., language), stored with your consent.</li>
        <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> If enabled, we use privacy-conscious analytics to understand usage; you can opt out or not consent.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="children">
      <h2>Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our services are intended for general audiences. If you are under the age required by applicable law to consent,
        please use the service with a parent or guardian, or provide consent documentation where required.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="international-transfers">
      <h2>International data transfers</h2>
      <p>
        If data is transferred outside the EU/EEA, we use appropriate safeguards (e.g., standard contractual clauses) to protect your information.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="contact">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy or security questions, or to exercise your rights, contact:
      </p>
      <address>
        <strong>Board Game Library — Privacy</strong><br />
        Email: privacy@boardgamelibrary.example<br />
        Location: Sønderborg, Region of Southern Denmark, Denmark
      </address>
    </section>

    <section id="updates">
      <h2>Policy updates</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Updates will be posted here with a revised date.
        Significant changes may be communicated via email or on-site notices.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>